message:
Fix a Java NPE crash when processing a parameter annotated with an annotation that placed in annotation package

This problem happens with KotlinPoet 1.7.x.
From KotlinPoet 1.7.x, `TypeName.toString()` is escaped with backquotes if the package name contains keywords.
So NPE will be thrown if an annotation is placed in `annotation` package because `elements.getTypeElement(it.typeName.toString())` returns `null`.

body: Good catch but this is sort of the wrong solution because it also doesn't work right? We should be grabbing the canonical classname

Ah, you are right.
Do you know of any code that can replace `TypeName.toString()` on KotlinPoet 1.7.x?
I'm not familiar with KotlinPoet, so if you know, please let me know.
Yep I think that's the right replacement to use

message: Move a test case of processing a qualifier placed in `annotation` package

I tried to create sample project to reproduce this issue, but for some reason this reproducing only in my work project. After some time I manage to find class which causes this crash and find to reproduce this crash I just have to add qualifier to any parameter in my class. So here is example of minimum test classes which causes this crash:
```kotlin
@JsonClass(generateAdapter = true)
data class TestDto(
    @TestQualifier val value: Int
)

@Retention(AnnotationRetention.RUNTIME)
@JsonQualifier
annotation class TestQualifier
```
